OL,3,CGaza documentary breached BBC
OL,4,Ceditorial guidelines of accuracy,
OL,5,Creview finds
OL,7,FThe review found no other breaches of
OL,8,Fthe guidelines nor any evidence that
OL,9,F'outside interests' "inappropriately
OL,10,Fimpacted on the programme".
OL,12,F"I have also not seen or heard any
OL,13,Fevidence to support a suggestion that
OL,14,Fthe narrator's father or family
OL,15,Finfluenced the content of the
OL,16,Fprogramme in any way," the report
OL,17,Fstated.
OL,19,FBut it found the use of a child
OL,20,Fnarrator for the programme was "wrong".
