OL,3,CGaza documentary breached BBC
OL,4,Ceditorial guidelines of accuracy,
OL,5,Creview finds
OL,7,FThe report stated the narrator "was
OL,8,Fput in a position where his narration
OL,9,Fhad to be highly scripted (meaning
OL,10,Fthere was a limited portrayal of his
OL,11,Fbackground, story and life) and where
OL,12,Fhe had to carry the rights-of-reply of
OL,13,Fothers, in particular the IDF".
OL,15,F"In light of what the production
OL,16,Fcompany knew about the narrator's
OL,17,Ffamily and background, putting him
OL,18,Fforward as the voice of the programme
OL,19,Fas it was scripted was wrong in my
OL,20,Fview."
